track_notes: Leaving the Hummingbird PRA campground hike south-west along the river, then start climbing to the ridge. Then follows a long ridgewalk along alternating patches of alpine vegetation and ankle-rolling boulders. Upon reaching the summit you can either retrace your steps, or bail to the bowl on the west side, then follow the river and cutlines back to campground. Do not follow this track exactly, much of the ridgewalk was done in dense fog.
